author: Jessica Estepa
description: The prime minister of Montenegro, who became the inadvertent star of a viral video of President Trump pushing him aside during a gathering of world leaders, called the incident "inoffensive."
title: President Trump's shove was 'inoffensive,' Montenegro prime minister says

description: BRUSSELS (AP) — President Donald Trump's push to get in front of the pack at a NATO summit generated indignation in the Balkans and garnered attention on social media — but the man he shoved aside took it in stride. At Thursday's gathering in Brussels, Trump put his right hand on the right arm of Montenegro Prime Minister Dusko Markovic and pushed himself ahead as NATO leaders walked inside the alliance's new headquarters and prepared for a group photo. Trump then stood near Markovic and spoke to Lithuanian President Dalia Grybauskaite. Video of the incident spread on social networks in multiple languages.
title: Trump pushes aside Montenegro leader _ who calls it natural

description: "This was an inoffensive situation,” Montenegro's prime minister told reporters. “I do not see it in any other way."
title: Breaking down Trump’s ‘shove’
